{{Infobox journal | title = Asian Culture | cover = | editors = [[Leo Suryadinata]], [[Neo Peng Fu]] | discipline = [[Asian studies]]; [[Interdisciplinary]] | peer-reviewed = | language = English, Chinese | abbreviation = Asian Cult. | publisher = [[Singapore Society of Asian Studies]] | country = [[Singapore]] | frequency = 1983–1989 (Bi-Annual), 1990–Present (Annual) | history = 1983–Present | openaccess = | license = | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://asianculturejournal.wordpress.com/ | link1 = | link1-name = | link2 = | link2-name = | RSS = | atom = | JSTOR = | OCLC = 607497422 | LCCN = | CODEN = | ISSN = 0217-6742 | eISSN = | boxwidth = }}
'''''Asian Culture''''' ('''''Yazhou Wenhua''''', '''亞洲文化''') is an international refereed bilingual academic journal of the [[Singapore Society of Asian Studies]]. It was inaugurated in 1983 as a bi-annual periodical and became an annual publication in 1990. ''Asian Culture'' publishes quality research papers in all aspects of Asian literature, history and philosophy. It is a well-regarded journal in the field of [[Southeast Asian studies]].
''Asian Culture'' has published a total of 39 issues by 2015. The current editors are [[Leo Suryadinata]] and [[Neo Peng Fu]].
