The '''East Turkestan Information Center''' ({{lang-ug|Sherqiy Türkistan Informatsiyon}}; [[Abbreviation|abbreviated]] '''ETIC''') is a group affiliated with the [[East Turkestan independence movement]]. It was founded in [[Munich]], [[Germany]] in 1996, and has an office in [[Washington, D.C.]]<ref>{{cite web|author=John Pike |url=http://www.globalsecurity.org/military/world/para/uighur.htm |title=Uighurs |publisher=Globalsecurity.org |date=2003-12-15 |accessdate=2012-10-09}}</ref>
The ETIC publishes reports on human rights violations and abuses by the [[Government of China|Chinese government]] towards China's ethnic [[Uyghur people|Uyghur]] population.<ref name="unhcr">{{cite web|author=United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees |url=http://www.unhcr.org/refworld/country,,EURASIANET,,CHN,,46c58f2f23,0.html |title=Refworld &#124; Kyrgyz rights activists call for end to deportation of Uighurs to China |publisher=UNHCR |date=2004-01-25 |accessdate=2012-10-09}}</ref>
On December 15 2003, the ETIC was designated as a terrorist organization by the [[Ministry of Public Security of the People's Republic of China]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.china-embassy.org/eng/xw/t56257.htm |title=China seeks int'l support in counter-terrorism(12/15/03) |publisher=China-embassy.org |date=2003-12-15 |accessdate=2012-10-09}}</ref> which [[Oxford Analytica]] says could be an excuse for repression of the Uyghur population.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oxan.com/display.aspx?ItemID=DB88349|title=China increases suppression in Xinjiang|publisher=Oxford Analytica|accessdate=2012-10-09}}</ref>
The ETIC's head, Abdujelil Karakash was quoted by the [[UNHCR]] saying:<ref name="unhcr"/> {{Quote|text=We have no connection with terrorists. Actually, China itself is a terrorist. It occupied our territory, our soil, our riches. Every day, it sends about 30,000 Chinese to East Turkestan, and 100 percent of them stay there.|sign=Abdujelil Karakash}}
