'''Heritage King''', formerly the ''King Local Architectural Conservation Advisory Committee'', is a conservation committee in [[King, Ontario|King Township]],<ref name="all">{{cite web|url=http://www.culture.gov.on.ca/english/culdiv/heritage/lacac_list.htm |title=Municipal Heritage Committees |publisher=Government of Ontario, Ministry of Culture |accessdate=2007-07-15 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070811123045/http://www.culture.gov.on.ca/english/culdiv/heritage/lacac_list.htm |archivedate=2007-08-11 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref> [[Ontario]], [[Canada]]. Consisting of between five and eleven members, with at least one township councillor, the committee advises council on local heritage matters. Founded in 1982, ''Heritage King'' exists by township by-law under the ''[[Ontario Heritage Act]]'',<ref name="OHA">{{cite web|url=http://www.e-laws.gov.on.ca/DBLaws/Statutes/English/90o18_e.htm#BK10 |title=Ontario Heritage Act |publisher=Queen's Printer, [[Government of Ontario]] |accessdate=2007-07-15 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070518135632/http://www.e-laws.gov.on.ca/DBLaws/Statutes/English/90o18_e.htm#BK10 |archivedate=2007-05-18 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.culture.gov.on.ca/english/culdiv/heritage/gea-bulletin.htm |title=Good News for Heritage: Improvements to the Ontario Heritage Act |publisher=Government of Ontario, [[Ministry of Culture (Ontario)|Ministry of Culture]] |accessdate=2007-07-15 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070218050924/http://www.culture.gov.on.ca/english/culdiv/heritage/gea-bulletin.htm |archivedate=2007-02-18 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref> which "''provides a framework within which municipalities can ensure the conservation of properties of cultural heritage value or interest''"<ref name="framework">{{cite|title=King Township History & Heritage|publisher=The Township of King Heritage Committee|date=May 2006 }}</ref>

