{{Infobox journal | title = Mexican Studies/Estudios Mexicanos | editor = [[Ruth Hellier-Tinoco]] | discipline = Multidisciplinary | language = English, Spanish | abbreviation = Mexican Stud. | publisher = [[University of California Press]] | country = United States | frequency = 3 issues/year | history = 1985–present | website = http://msem.ucpress.edu/ | ISSN = 0742-9797 }}
'''''Mexican Studies/Estudios Mexicanos''''' is a bilingual, [[peer reviewed]] [[academic journal]] covering [[Latin American studies|Mexican studies]]. Articles in both English and Spanish focus on the [[History of Mexico|history]], [[Politics of Mexico|politics]], [[Economy of Mexico|economy]], [[History of science and technology in Mexico|scientific development]], and the literature and arts of [[Mexico]]. The journal is published three times a year by [[University of California Press]] on behalf of the University of California Institute for Mexico and the United States (UCMEXUS), and the [[Universidad Nacional Autónoma de México]]. The current [[editor-in-chief]] is Ruth Hellier-Tinoco, who succeeded founding editor, Jaime Rodriguez O. The journal's editorial offices are located at [[University of California, Santa Barbara]].
